                        },
                        "displayName": "Jacob Wujciak-Jens",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Berlin"
                    },
                    "body": "I wasn't able to find any documentation on it out side of what is uploaded in root but I think [https://nightlies.apache.org/] should be the appropriate place? It should allow us to set up the required folder structure and does not have the issue of a ballooning git history. And we might be able to upload binaries from crossbow too (if infra allows it).",
